<section>
	<h2>But</h2>
	<p>This plugin makes an AJAX request when a form is submitted.</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Exemple</h2>
	<p>After the submission, check the network tab of console to see AJAX request sent.</p>

	<form class="provisional wb-onpage-submit" action="#target-address" method="POST">
		<div class="formContents">
			<div class="form-group">
				<label for="firstname"><span class="field-name">First Name</span></label>
				<input class="form-control" id="firstname" name="firstname" type="text" data-rule-minlength="2" />
			</div>
			<div class="form-group">
				<label for="lastname"><span class="field-name">Last Name</span></label>
				<input class="form-control" id="lastname" name="lastname" type="text" data-rule-minlength="2" />
			</div>
			<div class="form-group">
				<label for="preferredNumber">Preferred&nbsp;: <span class="field-name">Phone Number</span></label>
				<input class="form-control" id="preferredNumber" name="preferredNumber" type="tel" data-rule-phoneUS="true" />
			</div>
			<div class="form-group">
				<label for="email"><span class="field-name">Email Address</span> (test@domaine)</label>
				<input class="form-control" id="email" name="email" type="email" />
			</div>
			<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
		</div>
		<p class="successMessage hidden">Merci!</p>
		<p class="failureMessage hidden">Quelque chose a mal tourn√©</p>
	</form>

	<details class="mrgn-tp-md mrgn-bttm-md">
		<summary>View code</summary>
		<ol>
			<li>Create a <code>&lt;form&gt;</code> element and set <code>method</code> and <code>action</code> attributes
				<pre><code>&lt;form action="#target-link" method="POST"&gt;&lt;/form&gt;</code></pre>
			</li>
			<li>Within the <code>&lt;form&gt;</code> element, add <code>&lt;div class="formContents"&gt;</code>. This is where the inputs and buttons will go.
			</li>
			<li>Within the <code>&lt;div class="formContents"&gt;</code> element, add a submit <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> element with <code>class="provisioanl wb-onpage-submit"</code> and <code>type="submit"</code>.
				<pre><code>&lt;div class="formContents"&gt;&lt;button class="provisional wb-onpage-submit" type="submit"&gt;Submit&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
			</li>
			<li>Outside <code>&lt;div class="formContents"&gt;</code> element, add success and failure message with classes <code>class="successMessage hidden"</code> and <code>class="failureMessage hidden"</code>
			</li>
		</ol>
	</details>
</section>
